<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Pile1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Pile,</orth> subst. things heaped high together: <cit><quote>what --s of wealth hath he accumulated,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 3.2.107" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 III, 2, 107</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>in heaps and --s of ruin,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 3.1.207" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 1, 207</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to pick them in a p. of musty chaff,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 5.1.25" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 25</bibl></cit>. Particularly used of wood: <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.1.25" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. III, 1, 25</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 1.97" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 97</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 1.97" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 97</bibl>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>